==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wastrel
<hw>Wast"rel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Any waste
thing or substance</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Waste land or common
land.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Carew.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
profligate.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A
neglected child; a street Arab.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything cast away as bad or useless, as imperfect
bricks, china, etc.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Watch</ent>⟦br⟧
